WEBVTT

00:01.627 --> 00:03.879
<i>Previously on "The Rookie"...</i>
Bailey.
Jason.

00:03.879 --> 00:04.796
I'm John Nolan.
And you are?
Her husband.

00:04.796 --> 00:05.964
I'm trying
to protect this city.

00:05.964 --> 00:07.799
So you think putting
a 16‐year‐old into juvie

00:07.799 --> 00:10.135
is gonna turn the tide
in the war on drugs?

00:10.135 --> 00:12.638
I am in a good place.
James is great.

00:12.638 --> 00:14.014
What did you find out?

00:14.014 --> 00:15.891
Jason Wyler is the most charming
man on the planet.

00:15.891 --> 00:17.559
He whispers
in all the right ears,

00:17.559 --> 00:20.145
and whoever is his enemy ends up
on the wrong end of a shank.

00:20.145 --> 00:21.855
What is happening?
Why am I...

00:21.855 --> 00:23.398
He's framing me.

00:23.398 --> 00:25.859
Hearing that she's finally
facing some consequences,

00:25.859 --> 00:27.653
it does well
for my spirit.
I know
who you are now.

00:27.653 --> 00:29.404
And I'm coming for you.

00:29.404 --> 00:31.365
Bailey:
Let's talk about what's next.

00:31.365 --> 00:32.950
Well,
it's pretty straightforward.

00:32.950 --> 00:35.035
You can go to trial,
fight the charges,

00:35.035 --> 00:36.662
or take a plea.

00:36.662 --> 00:38.205
And if I fight
and lose?

00:38.205 --> 00:40.374
Most likely,
you'll do prison time.

00:40.374 --> 00:43.001
And if
I take a plea?

00:43.001 --> 00:45.128
I feel confident
that we could get

00:45.128 --> 00:47.673
a mandatory treatment program
and probation.

00:47.673 --> 00:50.634
But I would still have
a drug charge on my record,

00:50.634 --> 00:53.512
and at minimum, I would be
out of the Army Reserve

00:53.512 --> 00:57.432
and I'd probably be fired
from the LAFD.

00:57.432 --> 00:59.726
I would lose everything
that matters to me.

00:59.726 --> 01:01.019
Except for you.

01:02.479 --> 01:03.689
What?

01:03.689 --> 01:05.148
It's nothing.

01:05.148 --> 01:06.817
It's not nothing.

01:06.817 --> 01:09.361
And I can't take another round
of gaslighting right now.

01:09.361 --> 01:12.406
Okay, so,
the Department frowns

01:12.406 --> 01:15.409
on officers fraternizing
with convicted felons.

01:15.409 --> 01:18.704
They can frown all they want.
They can't fire me.

01:18.704 --> 01:21.039
Everyone who's important
knows you're innocent.

01:21.039 --> 01:23.875
But just dating me
would hold you back.

01:23.875 --> 01:25.085
[ Scoffs ]

01:25.085 --> 01:26.503
I gotta give it
to Jason ‐‐

01:26.503 --> 01:28.589
he really
planned this perfectly.

01:28.589 --> 01:31.341
You know, there is still
a third option.

01:31.341 --> 01:34.303
We prove your innocence
and we take him down.

01:37.931 --> 01:40.475
Morning.

01:41.810 --> 01:45.314
Um...what were you doing
up all night?

01:45.314 --> 01:46.940
Legal research.

01:46.940 --> 01:48.608
Researching what?

01:48.608 --> 01:51.236
Do you remember that, uh, kid I
was telling you about ‐‐ Tyler?

01:51.236 --> 01:52.904
Oh, the one
who robbed the liquor store...
Yes.

01:52.904 --> 01:55.115
...and then gave the store owner
a heart attack,

01:55.115 --> 01:57.617
and the clown from the DA's
office blamed you for it?

01:57.617 --> 02:00.120
No, I don't remember that.

02:01.330 --> 02:02.789
[ Chuckles ]

02:02.789 --> 02:04.207
Anyway, good news ‐‐

02:04.207 --> 02:05.876
um, the store owner
was released from the hospital.

02:05.876 --> 02:07.294
She's gonna be fine.
[ Coffee pours ]

02:07.294 --> 02:09.463
Amazing.
I bet Tyler's relieved.

02:09.463 --> 02:11.173
Yeah, but he's not
out of the woods yet.

02:11.173 --> 02:13.258
I have been up all night
trying to research ways

02:13.258 --> 02:14.968
that the state
can show him leniency.

02:14.968 --> 02:17.054
I've just got to convince
that clown

02:17.054 --> 02:18.597
to charge him as a minor.

02:18.597 --> 02:20.223
Well, Tyler's lucky he has you

02:20.223 --> 02:21.224
looking out for him.

02:21.224 --> 02:22.434
Aww.
I knew I was.

02:22.434 --> 02:23.769
Oh.
[ Chuckles ]

02:23.769 --> 02:25.145
I mean,
not that long ago,

02:25.145 --> 02:26.647
I was on the streets,
as desperate as he was,

02:26.647 --> 02:28.607
and then I did
the smartest thing

02:28.607 --> 02:30.859
I think I've ever done ‐‐
steal your car.

02:30.859 --> 02:33.153
Okay.
Agree to disagree.

02:33.153 --> 02:35.822
No, seriously.
Crime totally pays.

02:35.822 --> 02:37.032
And Tyler's lucky
to have you.

02:37.032 --> 02:39.284
You're cute!

02:39.284 --> 02:40.452
James: This is nice.

02:40.452 --> 02:43.288
Actually spending
the night together.

02:43.288 --> 02:46.249
Doing couple things
in the morning before work.

02:46.249 --> 02:48.293
Yeah, who knew we had to
share custody schedules

02:48.293 --> 02:49.336
before we hooked up?

02:49.336 --> 02:51.254
I actually should
get going, though.

02:51.254 --> 02:53.131
I gotta ‐‐
I gotta do a thing.

02:53.131 --> 02:54.466
That sounds ominous.

02:54.466 --> 02:55.634
No, it's fine.

02:55.634 --> 02:58.303
I just have to have a talk
with Curtis Jones.

02:58.303 --> 02:59.971
About Tyler.

02:59.971 --> 03:02.599
Wait. Is he still leaning
on Tyler's family for money?

03:02.599 --> 03:04.935
Yeah, and I‐I need
to convince Curtis

03:04.935 --> 03:06.978
to cut his losses
and let it go.

03:06.978 --> 03:08.689
Okay, well,
I'm coming with you.

03:08.689 --> 03:10.065
[ Chuckles ] No.

03:10.065 --> 03:12.526
Yes, I'm ‐‐
Nyla, no.

03:12.526 --> 03:13.694
No, you can't be there.

03:13.694 --> 03:15.070
Look, if ‐‐
if word gets out

03:15.070 --> 03:17.656
that a cop is hovering
on my shoulder,

03:17.656 --> 03:20.283
they'll stop trusting me.

03:20.283 --> 03:21.493
Well, I hate
to break it to you,

03:21.493 --> 03:23.537
but you're dating a cop,
so that's gonna get around.

03:23.537 --> 03:26.498
I know, which means
I have to work extra hard

03:26.498 --> 03:28.583
to stay independent.

03:28.583 --> 03:30.460
Look, if I lose the trust
with the community,

03:30.460 --> 03:32.546
I'll never get it back.

03:32.546 --> 03:34.381
I hear you,
but I don't like it.

03:34.381 --> 03:36.174
And Curtis
is a dangerous guy,

03:36.174 --> 03:38.301
and if anything
were to happen to you,

03:38.301 --> 03:41.680
I'd be sad for, like,
at least a couple days.

03:41.680 --> 03:42.931
[ Chuckles ]

03:42.931 --> 03:44.015
Funny. Funny.

03:44.015 --> 03:46.059
But I can handle myself.

03:46.059 --> 03:47.686
Alright?

03:47.686 --> 03:49.688
I'll call you after.

03:50.772 --> 03:53.191
I wish we could open an official
investigation on this.

03:53.191 --> 03:54.526
No, sir, I get it.

03:54.526 --> 03:56.361
There's not even
circumstantial evidence

03:56.361 --> 03:58.405
connecting Jason
to planting those drugs.

03:58.405 --> 04:01.116
Thank you, again,
for authorizing my...

04:01.116 --> 04:02.242
"vacation."

04:02.242 --> 04:03.034
Of course.

04:03.034 --> 04:05.287
Take as much time as you need.

04:05.287 --> 04:06.496
So, what's your plan?

04:06.496 --> 04:07.873
Find the money.

04:07.873 --> 04:10.375
I mean, those drugs cost upwards
of 10 grand,

04:10.375 --> 04:12.419
but according to my skip tracer,
Jason's broke.

04:12.419 --> 04:15.046
He had to pay restitution
for his embezzlement conviction,

04:15.046 --> 04:16.506
and he's been working
a minimum‐wage job

04:16.506 --> 04:18.049
ever since his release.

04:18.049 --> 04:20.510
So chances are, he's mixed up
in something illegal

04:20.510 --> 04:23.096
that gives him access
to money or drugs or both.

04:23.096 --> 04:25.432
And I'm gonna follow him till
I find out exactly what it is.

04:25.432 --> 04:27.517
Call me as soon as you have
something actionable,

04:27.517 --> 04:30.103
even if it's a simple
parole violation.

04:30.103 --> 04:32.647
Once he's in custody,
he's more likely to crack.

04:32.647 --> 04:34.733
[ Cellphone chimes ]

04:34.733 --> 04:36.151
I gotta go.

04:36.151 --> 04:37.486
Caught a homicide.

04:37.486 --> 04:39.112
Let me know
if you need anything.
Thank you.

04:39.112 --> 04:40.864
So, listen, Nolan,

04:40.864 --> 04:43.158
there's something you need
to think about.

04:43.158 --> 04:45.076
[ Door closes ]
If Bailey assumes fault
for the drugs ‐‐

04:45.076 --> 04:46.495
I know.

04:46.495 --> 04:48.330
If I can't prove
Jason planted those drugs,

04:48.330 --> 04:49.956
I'll have to choose
between my career

04:49.956 --> 04:52.125
and the woman I love.

04:52.125 --> 04:54.002
No biggie.

04:54.002 --> 04:56.087
Thanks.

04:56.087 --> 04:57.923
ADA Sanford.

04:57.923 --> 04:59.382
Officer Chen.

04:59.382 --> 05:00.759
Did you hear the news?

05:00.759 --> 05:03.720
The store owner from
Tyler's case pulled through.

05:03.720 --> 05:05.305
I heard.
Mm‐hmm.

05:05.305 --> 05:06.389
I'm as relieved
as you are.

05:06.389 --> 05:08.266
Great.

05:08.266 --> 05:10.268
So, let's continue
with the positivity.

05:10.268 --> 05:12.062
Charge Tyler as a minor.

05:12.062 --> 05:14.314
He committed a crime
with a gun.

05:14.314 --> 05:15.690
It was unloaded.

05:15.690 --> 05:18.443
Look, I'm not saying that
there shouldn't be consequences,

05:18.443 --> 05:20.070
but he's 16.

05:20.070 --> 05:21.863
He's not old enough
to drink, vote,

05:21.863 --> 05:23.406
join the military,

05:23.406 --> 05:25.534
and you want to lock him up
with a bunch of grown men?

05:25.534 --> 05:26.993
Look,
studies show that ‐‐

05:26.993 --> 05:28.870
No, please,
don't quote studies at me.

05:28.870 --> 05:30.831
And definitely
don't start lecturing me

05:30.831 --> 05:32.457
about the science
of still‐developing brains

05:32.457 --> 05:33.708
in men under 21.

05:33.708 --> 05:35.460
I wasn't gonna do that.

05:35.460 --> 05:37.003
[ Scoffs ]

05:37.003 --> 05:39.589
Look, if Tyler becomes a CI
against his crew,

05:39.589 --> 05:41.424
I can definitely
give him a break.

05:41.424 --> 05:43.593
Uh...wait. S‐Sorry.

05:43.593 --> 05:45.178
Let me ‐‐
Let me just get this clear.

05:45.178 --> 05:46.972
So, instead of risking his life
in prison,

05:46.972 --> 05:48.849
you want to risk his life
on the streets?

05:48.849 --> 05:51.560
Do you understand that he is
a low‐level drug runner?

05:51.560 --> 05:53.603
He is the bottom
of the food chain.

05:53.603 --> 05:54.938
Nobody in his crew

05:54.938 --> 05:56.857
is gonna even trust him
with any real intel.

05:56.857 --> 05:58.358
Everything okay?

05:58.358 --> 05:59.651
Yes.

05:59.651 --> 06:01.236
Mr., uh,
Rookie ADA here

06:01.236 --> 06:03.572
was telling me
how he was gonna make his bones

06:03.572 --> 06:06.324
by ending a kid's life.
Okay.

06:06.324 --> 06:08.869
You're clearly feeling
a little dramatic this morning,

06:08.869 --> 06:10.871
and I have to go
to court.

06:12.372 --> 06:13.582
[ Chuckles ]

06:13.582 --> 06:16.626
I will be
following up with you!

06:16.626 --> 06:19.462
Can you believe the nerve of
that guy, calling <i>me</i> dramatic?

06:19.462 --> 06:21.464
I mean ‐‐
Um, do not start.

06:21.464 --> 06:24.134
Exactly how many cups of coffee
did you have this morning?

06:24.134 --> 06:27.012
I'm just going to
apologize to you right now.

06:27.012 --> 06:28.638
Um, it's gonna be
a really long day for you,

06:28.638 --> 06:30.557
and ‐‐ and I'm sorry.
[ Sighs deeply ]

06:30.557 --> 06:32.851
Aaron.
Mom,
what are you doing here?

06:32.851 --> 06:34.811
Hi, baby.
Mwah.

06:34.811 --> 06:36.855
Look at you
in this uniform.

06:36.855 --> 06:38.899
How handsome.

06:38.899 --> 06:41.610
Look, I said no yesterday,
and I meant it, okay?

06:41.610 --> 06:43.236
Uh‐huh.
So please stop asking.

06:43.236 --> 06:44.529
But you're not
thinking it through.

06:44.529 --> 06:45.947
The hell I'm not.

06:45.947 --> 06:47.407
Whoa.
What's the problem?
Nothing.

06:47.407 --> 06:48.742
Just having a conversation
with my mother.

06:49.743 --> 06:52.537
Now I know you did not
just speak to your
mother in that tone.

06:52.537 --> 06:55.915
Ma'am, I am Nyla Harper,
Aaron's training officer,

06:55.915 --> 06:58.543
and he is going to apologize
to you right now,

06:58.543 --> 07:00.003
or I will write him up

07:00.003 --> 07:02.380
for conduct
unbecoming of an officer.

07:02.380 --> 07:04.424
[ Scoffs ]

07:05.717 --> 07:07.093
I'm sorry.

07:07.093 --> 07:08.803
Thank you.

07:08.803 --> 07:10.055
And thank you, Nyla.

07:10.055 --> 07:12.098
Of course, Mrs. Thorsen.
It's Yvonne.

07:12.098 --> 07:14.392
Yvonne.

07:14.392 --> 07:15.685
See you in the shop.

07:15.685 --> 07:17.520
Oh.
I like her.

07:17.520 --> 07:19.522
Look, Mom...
I like her.

07:19.522 --> 07:21.149
...I'm sorry
for going off, okay?

07:21.149 --> 07:23.068
But I don't want to be a part
of this reality TV show.

07:23.068 --> 07:25.654
Sweetie,
it's only gonna help you.
How?

07:25.654 --> 07:28.323
By disrespecting
the memory of Patrick?

07:28.323 --> 07:29.824
By trivializing the time
I've spent in prison

07:29.824 --> 07:31.117
for a crime
I didn't commit?

07:31.117 --> 07:32.952
Not if we
control the narrative.

07:32.952 --> 07:35.330
Mom,
I love you, okay?

07:35.330 --> 07:36.956
You've been on my side
through everything,

07:36.956 --> 07:38.583
but the answer's no.

07:38.583 --> 07:39.918
Now I have to go.

07:43.004 --> 07:44.923
♪♪

07:44.923 --> 07:47.759
[ Insects buzzing ]

07:47.759 --> 07:50.637
I think this may be
our strangest date yet.

07:50.637 --> 07:51.930
Really?

07:51.930 --> 07:53.723
Stranger than fighting
a Russian spy?

07:53.723 --> 07:56.726
We're surveilling
your ex‐con current husband

07:56.726 --> 07:58.770
who has framed you
for a drug crime.

07:58.770 --> 08:01.648
<i>Estranged</i> ex‐con
current husband.

08:01.648 --> 08:03.608
[ Cellphone rings ]
Oh, good.

08:03.608 --> 08:05.985
Hey, Randy.
Randy:
<i>Skip Tracer Randy here!</i>

08:05.985 --> 08:08.863
Yes. I know, Randy.
I said your name.

08:08.863 --> 08:10.699
<i>Oh, well, maybe you know</i>
<i>12 Randys. I don't know.</i>

08:10.699 --> 08:12.325
<i>Would you like to know</i>
<i>what I found,</i>

08:12.325 --> 08:13.952
<i>or do you want to keep</i>
<i>making me feel bad</i>

08:13.952 --> 08:15.370
<i>about how I put myself out</i>
<i>in the world?</i>

08:15.370 --> 08:17.038
No. No.
Randy, you're right.

08:17.038 --> 08:18.832
I'm sorry.
What did you get?

08:18.832 --> 08:21.793
<i>Jason listed an SRO downtown</i>
<i>as his current address,</i>

08:21.793 --> 08:23.253
<i>but the man</i>
<i>at the front desk says</i>

08:23.253 --> 08:25.004
<i>he's only seen him</i>
<i>once or twice.</i>

08:25.004 --> 08:26.381
So, he could be staying
somewhere else.

08:26.381 --> 08:27.632
That could be a violation
of his parole.

08:27.632 --> 08:28.800
Mm‐hmm.
<i>That is correct.</i>

08:28.800 --> 08:30.760
<i>I'll call back</i>
<i>if I find anything else.</i>

08:30.760 --> 08:32.011
Thank you, Randy.

08:32.011 --> 08:33.638
Well, that makes sense.

08:33.638 --> 08:34.973
Jason is a total snob.

08:34.973 --> 08:36.474
[ Sighs ]

08:36.474 --> 08:38.268
Is this really
the best we can do?

08:38.268 --> 08:39.811
Just spy on him

08:39.811 --> 08:42.355
until he hopefully
does something overtly criminal?

08:42.355 --> 08:44.065
Welcome to police work.

08:44.065 --> 08:46.026
We're never gonna catch him
by being reactive.

08:46.026 --> 08:48.486
He's too smart.
We have to get in his head.

08:48.486 --> 08:51.406
If that's really
what you want to do,

08:51.406 --> 08:53.033
I know who to talk to,

08:53.033 --> 08:55.076
but it would
officially cement this

08:55.076 --> 08:58.747
as 1,000%
the strangest date yet.

08:58.747 --> 09:00.415
Well,
when you put it that way...

09:00.415 --> 09:02.709
[ Door buzzes ]
[ Chuckles ]

09:02.709 --> 09:05.336
At this point, you should
probably deputize me.

09:07.380 --> 09:08.798
Hello.

09:08.798 --> 09:10.341
Who did you bring for me,
John?

09:10.341 --> 09:12.177
Oscar, this is
Lieutenant Nune.

09:12.177 --> 09:13.178
Bailey.

09:13.178 --> 09:15.680
I'm Jason Wyler's...
wife.

09:15.680 --> 09:17.057
Well, I'd salute you,

09:17.057 --> 09:18.475
but I can't get my arm
over my shoulder.

09:18.475 --> 09:20.810
I'm told
you're an expert

09:20.810 --> 09:22.979
in narcissist psychopaths.

09:22.979 --> 09:24.564
Guilty as charged.

09:24.564 --> 09:25.899
Literally.

09:25.899 --> 09:28.068
We need your help
to get inside his head,

09:28.068 --> 09:29.569
figure out
what he's gonna do next.

09:29.569 --> 09:31.237
And I would love
to do that.

09:31.237 --> 09:33.740
I just need to figure out
what I get out of it.

09:33.740 --> 09:35.241
Oscar.

09:35.241 --> 09:38.119
I wrote a letter to get you
transferred out of here.

09:38.119 --> 09:39.746
And that's
what I got yesterday.

09:39.746 --> 09:41.414
Let's discuss
what I get today.

09:41.414 --> 09:42.916
Today, I go
to the Warden's office

09:42.916 --> 09:45.043
and rip up
yesterday's letter.
You're bluffing.

09:45.043 --> 09:46.336
Let's go.

09:46.336 --> 09:47.921
Okay, fine.
I'll help you.

09:47.921 --> 09:49.839
Um, alright,
where do we stand?

09:49.839 --> 09:51.883
Jason and I
were married for a year

09:51.883 --> 09:53.551
before he went
to prison.

09:53.551 --> 09:56.513
During that time,
he was psychologically abusive,

09:56.513 --> 09:58.389
he tore me down
constantly

09:58.389 --> 10:01.226
and terrorized me
when I asked for a divorce.

10:01.226 --> 10:03.561
Two weeks ago,
he got out of jail

10:03.561 --> 10:05.814
and set out
to ruin my life.

10:05.814 --> 10:08.608
He planted drugs in her car
and got her arrested.
Okay.

10:08.608 --> 10:10.985
So,
he's highly intelligent,

10:10.985 --> 10:13.780
he's very good
at getting inside people's heads

10:13.780 --> 10:15.949
and pitting people
against one another.

10:15.949 --> 10:17.909
He's also deeply insecure.

10:17.909 --> 10:19.953
That's why he's constantly
pounding you down,

10:19.953 --> 10:21.246
making you small.

10:21.246 --> 10:23.164
It's the only way
he can make himself big.

10:23.164 --> 10:24.833
How do we use that
against him?

10:26.126 --> 10:28.086
Well, best way
to throw him off of his game

10:28.086 --> 10:31.172
is...demean him.

10:31.172 --> 10:32.924
Make him feel stupid.

10:32.924 --> 10:34.384
Belittle him.

10:34.384 --> 10:37.345
Of course, he's gonna retaliate,
like, ten‐fold.

10:37.345 --> 10:39.722
How did he get his hands on
those drugs in the first place?

10:39.722 --> 10:42.100
Probably a contact
in prison.

10:42.100 --> 10:45.395
Whoever it was he was paying
for protection on the inside.

10:45.395 --> 10:47.689
But he wouldn't have gotten
the drugs for free.

10:47.689 --> 10:49.107
Well, it's not hard
to get money,

10:49.107 --> 10:50.775
I mean, if you're willing
to con someone.

10:50.775 --> 10:52.193
In fact,
there's an entire network

10:52.193 --> 10:53.653
of nightingales
out there

10:53.653 --> 10:56.072
that are just waiting
to help rehabilitate

10:56.072 --> 10:58.158
some poor,
misunderstood man.

10:58.158 --> 10:59.826
Speaking
from experience?

10:59.826 --> 11:02.495
I get a little money
in my commissary account.

11:02.495 --> 11:05.456
They get
a romantic fantasy.

11:05.456 --> 11:09.210
I mean...
everybody wins.

11:09.210 --> 11:11.838
Now, your boy, though,
he's playing the long game.

11:11.838 --> 11:14.757
He's probably targeted
a dozen or so women

11:14.757 --> 11:16.342
just to find
the right one.

11:16.342 --> 11:18.428
The warden will have copies
of all of Jason's mail.

11:18.428 --> 11:19.637
We can start there.

11:19.637 --> 11:20.930
Yeah.

11:20.930 --> 11:24.809
[ Siren wails,
police chatter ]

11:31.900 --> 11:34.360
Alright.
Thank you.

11:34.360 --> 11:36.529
Thanks.
You called us?

11:36.529 --> 11:38.198
Yeah,
a jogger found a female DB

11:38.198 --> 11:39.490
under the overpass.

11:39.490 --> 11:41.868
Blunt force trauma to the head.
Dump job.

11:41.868 --> 11:44.078
Looks like she's been here
about 24 hours.

11:44.078 --> 11:47.207
Found an ID on her.
Rebecca Price, 18 years old.

11:47.207 --> 11:48.416
Sounds like
you got it handled.

11:48.416 --> 11:50.335
What do you need
a sergeant for?

11:50.335 --> 11:52.295
I don't.
I need Lucy.

11:52.295 --> 11:54.547
Do you know her?

11:54.547 --> 11:56.299
No. Uh, why?

11:56.299 --> 11:58.760
Your roommate does.

12:03.598 --> 12:08.102
[ <i>Music playing in distance</i> ]

12:08.102 --> 12:09.812
Alright, how do you want
to handle this?

12:09.812 --> 12:11.231
I don't know.

12:11.231 --> 12:13.024
I've ‐‐ I've never delivered
a death notification

12:13.024 --> 12:15.401
to someone I care about.

12:15.401 --> 12:17.570
♪♪

12:17.570 --> 12:18.863
I know what to do
as a cop,

12:18.863 --> 12:20.406
and I know how to do it
as a roommate,

12:20.406 --> 12:22.909
but, you know,
those are different approaches.

12:22.909 --> 12:24.577
Just be a friend.

12:24.577 --> 12:26.913
And if you need a cop,
tag me in.

12:26.913 --> 12:29.290
Thank you.
Mm‐hmm.

12:29.290 --> 12:30.708
[ Knock on door ]
Come in.

12:30.708 --> 12:32.210
[ <i>Music stops</i> ]

12:32.210 --> 12:34.587
Forget something?

12:34.587 --> 12:36.256
No.

12:36.256 --> 12:38.549
[ Door closes ]

12:38.549 --> 12:41.886
They found a body
this morning.

12:44.389 --> 12:47.392
It was your friend.
Becca.

12:47.392 --> 12:49.102
What?

12:49.102 --> 12:50.436
No.

12:50.436 --> 12:51.854
I'm sorry.

12:51.854 --> 12:53.273
No, no, no.

12:53.273 --> 12:55.066
No, i‐it can't be her.
[ Chuckles ]

12:55.066 --> 12:56.651
It wasn't Becca.
I'll call her.

12:56.651 --> 13:00.655
I'm sorry.
It definitely was her.

13:00.655 --> 13:03.157
There was a photo
of the two of you on her phone.

13:03.157 --> 13:05.618
♪♪

13:05.618 --> 13:08.413
Oh, look.
Here's one of mine.

13:08.413 --> 13:10.915
A desperate plea
to respond to my lawyer.

13:10.915 --> 13:12.292
Fun memento.

13:12.292 --> 13:14.794
Here's one from Jason
to an Evelyn Reed.

13:14.794 --> 13:18.298
"When we met, I was so broken.
You healed me."

13:18.298 --> 13:21.259
Oh, he's still using
the same material he used on me.

13:21.259 --> 13:23.219
I can't believe
I was this stupid.

13:23.219 --> 13:26.556
No, you weren't stupid.
You were just...trusting.

13:26.556 --> 13:28.599
Here's one from Evelyn
back to Jason.

13:28.599 --> 13:31.060
"Dear Jason, I must have
read your last letter

13:31.060 --> 13:32.437
a thousand times.

13:32.437 --> 13:34.689
Though steel bars
may separate our bodies,

13:34.689 --> 13:36.649
they can't separate
our souls."

13:36.649 --> 13:37.817
Barf.

13:37.817 --> 13:39.319
But that does
sound like someone

13:39.319 --> 13:40.778
who would do anything
for him.

13:40.778 --> 13:42.196
What's her address?

13:42.196 --> 13:44.866
Lucy: Did Becca ever mention
someone she was scared of?

13:44.866 --> 13:47.243
No.

13:47.243 --> 13:49.495
But we haven't talked
in a while.

13:49.495 --> 13:51.956
Almost three months.

13:51.956 --> 13:54.500
With school
and moving in here,

13:54.500 --> 13:55.918
I just lost track.

13:55.918 --> 13:58.629
Okay, any idea
where she was crashing?

13:58.629 --> 14:00.548
[ Sighs ]

14:00.548 --> 14:02.675
She mostly lived
on the street.

14:02.675 --> 14:05.970
There was a shelter
that sometimes had room.

14:05.970 --> 14:08.306
And a couple of kids
who had families

14:08.306 --> 14:10.141
who'd let you
sleep on the floor

14:10.141 --> 14:11.517
every once in a while.

14:11.517 --> 14:13.853
And if you were
desperate enough,

14:13.853 --> 14:15.354
there was always swiping.

14:17.023 --> 14:18.775
What's that?

14:20.526 --> 14:23.696
You go on ClipTalk
and just swipe

14:23.696 --> 14:25.865
until you find someone
to hook up with.

14:25.865 --> 14:27.867
And if you're lucky,

14:27.867 --> 14:31.537
you might get a warm shower
and a meal

14:31.537 --> 14:33.039
when it's all over.

14:33.039 --> 14:34.749
Tim: Okay, if she was still
doing that,

14:34.749 --> 14:36.334
we need a list of the guys
she met up with.

14:36.334 --> 14:37.960
I'll reach out
to the tech department,

14:37.960 --> 14:39.337
see if they can
get into her account.

14:39.337 --> 14:41.964
No. I bet
I can guess her password.

14:41.964 --> 14:43.633
Harper: So, what's the deal
with your mom?

14:43.633 --> 14:46.385
[ Sighs ] That is a long
and boring story.

14:46.385 --> 14:48.387
Which stakeouts
are made for.

14:48.387 --> 14:49.847
Oh, is that
what we're doing here?

14:49.847 --> 14:51.140
Who are we staking out?

14:51.140 --> 14:52.517
We're just keeping an eye
on a friend.

14:52.517 --> 14:53.851
Is it
one of those guys?

14:53.851 --> 14:55.186
Stop trying
to change the subject.

14:55.186 --> 14:57.188
You and your mom.
Look, it's complicated.

14:57.188 --> 14:58.523
You're gonna have to threaten me
with a blue page

14:58.523 --> 14:59.732
if you want me
to say any more.

14:59.732 --> 15:02.235
Alright.
Fair enough.

15:03.236 --> 15:05.571
Oh,
<i>now</i> it makes sense.

15:05.571 --> 15:07.406
Why didn't you just say
we was here to watch
your boyfriend's back?

15:07.406 --> 15:09.826
Look, James is looking out
for a neighborhood kid.

15:09.826 --> 15:11.702
He's pushing back
against a local dealer,

15:11.702 --> 15:14.038
so we are here in case
anything goes sideways.

15:14.038 --> 15:17.041
Look, I heard you're still
trying to collect Tyler's debt

15:17.041 --> 15:18.376
from some
of his family members.

15:18.376 --> 15:19.710
The kid owes me.

15:19.710 --> 15:21.003
Curtis,
he ‐‐ he's in jail

15:21.003 --> 15:22.713
'cause he tried
to get your money.

15:22.713 --> 15:24.799
It's not my fault he can't
stick up a liquor store.

15:24.799 --> 15:25.883
[ Sighs ]

15:25.883 --> 15:27.385
[ Clatter ]

15:27.385 --> 15:29.929
Uh, Harper.

15:29.929 --> 15:31.264
You have got
to be kidding me.

15:31.264 --> 15:32.890
I assume
we should stop him, yeah?

15:32.890 --> 15:34.851
[ Sighs ]

15:34.851 --> 15:38.146
7‐Adam‐19,
Code 6 on a 459.

15:38.146 --> 15:41.732
Suspect is a Hispanic male,
blue jeans, grey jacket.

15:41.732 --> 15:43.693
♪♪

15:43.693 --> 15:44.819
Hey!

15:44.819 --> 15:47.572
Stop right there!
Stop! Hey!

15:47.572 --> 15:49.907
♪ I'm laying in this single bed,
but I can't sleep ♪

15:49.907 --> 15:52.618
♪ There must be more to life
than Tinder swipes ♪

15:52.618 --> 15:55.163
♪ And posting...on Instagram
for meaningless likes ♪

15:55.163 --> 15:57.123
♪ Where I'm from, there's teen
mums sipping booze ♪

15:57.123 --> 15:59.625
♪ Whilst the baby takes twos
on her B&H blues ♪

15:59.625 --> 16:01.919
♪ The boys are in gangs,
the girls push prams ♪

16:01.919 --> 16:04.589
♪ And spend all their money
on some...fake tans ♪

16:04.589 --> 16:06.507
♪ I know I've got to get ‐‐ ♪
[ Gasps ]

16:07.383 --> 16:09.051
Hey.
You okay?

16:09.051 --> 16:10.469
You alright?

16:10.469 --> 16:11.888
You okay?
You okay?

16:11.888 --> 16:13.181
[ Winces ]
[ Baby cries ]

16:13.181 --> 16:15.600
Oh, that's deep.
You're gonna need stitches.

16:15.600 --> 16:17.268
[ Sighs ]
Yeah, and couple's therapy.

16:17.268 --> 16:18.936
I don't follow.
[ Sighs ]

16:18.936 --> 16:20.897
I promised James
I'd mind my own business.

16:20.897 --> 16:22.148
Yeah,
you're definitely busted.

16:22.148 --> 16:23.816
7‐Adam‐19.

16:23.816 --> 16:26.819
I need additional units
to follow our 459 suspect,

16:26.819 --> 16:29.113
last seen
at Grant and Lennox.

16:29.113 --> 16:32.533
I also need an RA
for an injured officer.

16:32.533 --> 16:35.661
Alright, Lopez sent a PDF
of Becca's ClipTalk account.

16:35.661 --> 16:37.288
It looks like
she was routinely hooking up

16:37.288 --> 16:38.873
with four different guys.

16:38.873 --> 16:40.333
No DMs indicating

16:40.333 --> 16:42.126
that they made plans
to meet up in the past week.

16:42.126 --> 16:43.628
Yeah, well, Lopez should
look into all of them.

16:43.628 --> 16:47.131
ClipTalk might not be
the only way they communicate.

16:47.131 --> 16:48.799
You okay?

16:48.799 --> 16:51.260
Yeah, Tamara knew about
the whole swiping thing,

16:51.260 --> 16:52.637
like, right away.

16:52.637 --> 16:53.846
Did you
get the impression

16:53.846 --> 16:56.307
that maybe
she used to do it herself?

16:56.307 --> 16:58.351
She ever
mention it to you?

16:58.351 --> 16:59.852
As close as we are,

16:59.852 --> 17:01.520
there's a lot
she won't talk about.

17:01.520 --> 17:03.189
Don't take it personally.

17:03.189 --> 17:05.858
She might just have a hard time
opening up to you.

17:05.858 --> 17:08.236
But I'm sure Tamara will share
when she's ready to.

17:09.320 --> 17:10.863
[ Doorbell rings ]

17:10.863 --> 17:12.865
Who are you?

17:12.865 --> 17:14.742
I'm Jason's wife.
Right.

17:14.742 --> 17:16.077
The bitch who won't
give him a divorce

17:16.077 --> 17:17.411
'cause she's obsessed,

17:17.411 --> 17:18.704
and you're
the crooked cop boyfriend.

17:18.704 --> 17:20.039
Excuse me?
Okay.

17:20.039 --> 17:22.166
Ma'am,
none of that is true.

17:22.166 --> 17:24.502
May we come in
and talk?
Hell no.

17:24.502 --> 17:27.672
Ms. Reed, Jason is a dangerous
and manipulative man

17:27.672 --> 17:29.966
who may be involved
in illegal activities.

17:29.966 --> 17:32.134
[ Scoffs ] Lies.
Okay, how about this?

17:32.134 --> 17:33.511
Is Jason living here?

17:33.511 --> 17:34.845
Because if he is,

17:34.845 --> 17:36.889
he has not reported this address
to his PO,

17:36.889 --> 17:38.683
which means I can report
the violation of his parole

17:38.683 --> 17:40.017
in one phone call.

17:40.017 --> 17:41.310
If you've aided in
any of the crimes

17:41.310 --> 17:42.520
he's committed
in any way,

17:42.520 --> 17:45.356
you can be charged
as an accessory.

17:45.356 --> 17:48.943
Or...how about
we just talk?

17:48.943 --> 17:50.570
[ Door opens ]

17:50.570 --> 17:52.405
Jason said
that you might try

17:52.405 --> 17:55.950
to get me
to turn on him.

17:55.950 --> 17:57.410
It isn't gonna work,

17:57.410 --> 18:00.204
so come in and say
whatever you have to say,

18:00.204 --> 18:02.206
and then go.

18:02.206 --> 18:04.750
He told you about
his mother, right?

18:04.750 --> 18:06.168
How close they were?

18:06.168 --> 18:08.170
How broken he was
when she died?

18:08.170 --> 18:09.547
May I sit?

18:09.547 --> 18:11.007
Uh‐huh.

18:12.049 --> 18:16.012
That was what first drew me
to him.

18:16.012 --> 18:18.055
That depth of feeling.

18:18.055 --> 18:19.390
When we first met,

18:19.390 --> 18:22.560
my father had just died,
and I was a wreck.

18:22.560 --> 18:25.605
Jason was the only person
who understood.

18:25.605 --> 18:28.774
He didn't try to fix me.
He just listened.

18:28.774 --> 18:32.069
He held my hand,
made me his entire world.

18:32.069 --> 18:34.447
So I made him mine.

18:34.447 --> 18:37.992
I had no one else
but him.

18:37.992 --> 18:41.287
And he started
chipping away at me.

18:41.287 --> 18:44.081
I wasn't smart enough,

18:44.081 --> 18:46.459
thin enough,
pretty enough.

18:46.459 --> 18:50.546
But I was lucky
to have him...

18:50.546 --> 18:53.215
because who else
could ever want me?

18:53.215 --> 18:56.385
♪♪

18:56.385 --> 18:59.472
[ Inhales shakily ]

18:59.472 --> 19:01.390
I wanted to die.

19:01.390 --> 19:03.309
♪♪

19:03.309 --> 19:07.313
I was even planning
how I would do it.

19:07.313 --> 19:09.857
That was when
I finally woke up.

19:09.857 --> 19:11.484
I'm sorry.

19:11.484 --> 19:15.196
♪♪

19:15.196 --> 19:17.281
Forgive me for asking.

19:17.281 --> 19:19.909
Is Jason's car
in your name?
Yeah.

19:19.909 --> 19:21.369
Because he's an ex‐con,

19:21.369 --> 19:24.288
so he said it would be hard
for him to get a loan.

19:24.288 --> 19:27.041
Has he ever asked you
to make large cash deposits?

19:27.041 --> 19:29.460
Yes.
And where do you think
that money comes from?

19:29.460 --> 19:30.961
I didn't ask.

19:30.961 --> 19:32.546
Has he ever asked you
to buy a gun?

19:33.631 --> 19:35.132
Am I in trouble?

19:35.132 --> 19:37.885
Not if you help us.

19:40.388 --> 19:41.847
So sorry
to keep you waiting.

19:41.847 --> 19:43.974
Yeah, uh, I'm all stitched
and ready to go,

19:43.974 --> 19:45.518
so why did I have to
hang around?

19:45.518 --> 19:47.103
Your lab work
came back,

19:47.103 --> 19:49.313
and I wanted
to talk to you about it.

19:49.313 --> 19:50.523
What?

19:50.523 --> 19:52.066
Am I ‐‐
Am I sick or something?

19:52.066 --> 19:53.693
No.

19:53.693 --> 19:55.403
You're six weeks pregnant.

20:00.825 --> 20:02.743
[ Sighs ]
There you go.

20:02.743 --> 20:04.203
It's all yours.
Thank you.

20:04.203 --> 20:05.705
We really
appreciate this.

20:05.705 --> 20:07.873
I'm just ‐‐
I'm glad I found out the truth

20:07.873 --> 20:09.208
before it was
too late.

20:09.208 --> 20:11.669
Oh,
there's one more thing.

20:11.669 --> 20:12.753
Alright, you think
there's something in here

20:12.753 --> 20:14.463
we can use
against him?

20:14.463 --> 20:16.465
Well, Jason is good,
but he's far from perfect.

20:16.465 --> 20:17.967
He's gonna mess up
at some point.

20:17.967 --> 20:19.635
We just need to be there
when he does.

20:19.635 --> 20:21.178
[ Door opens ]
Jason: Hey. I'm home

20:21.178 --> 20:22.847
and I'm starving.

20:22.847 --> 20:26.142
♪♪

20:26.142 --> 20:28.686
What the hell
are you doing here?

20:28.686 --> 20:30.479
Th‐‐
This is harassment, alright?

20:30.479 --> 20:32.106
Uh, you ‐‐ you both need
to leave.

20:32.106 --> 20:34.024
You okay, babe?

20:34.024 --> 20:36.193
You don't have to listen to
them, you know? You have rights.

20:36.193 --> 20:38.070
I know.

20:40.072 --> 20:41.574
Get out.

20:41.574 --> 20:43.534
What?
Oh, come on.

20:43.534 --> 20:45.745
I to‐‐ I told you,
they're trying to frame me.

20:45.745 --> 20:48.247
Now, you are too smart
to fall for whatever it is

20:48.247 --> 20:49.540
that they're trying
to tell you.

20:49.540 --> 20:50.875
Bailey
told me everything.

20:50.875 --> 20:54.044
You used all the same lies on
her that you used on me.

20:54.044 --> 20:58.048
Bailey is
a very sick woman,

20:58.048 --> 20:59.592
a drug addict,
paranoid, delusional ‐‐

20:59.592 --> 21:01.385
No, I need you
to leave now.

21:01.385 --> 21:04.555
This is my house,
and I want you to leave.

21:04.555 --> 21:06.223
And don't bother
coming back.

21:06.223 --> 21:08.225
A restraining order will be
filed before you hit the street.

21:08.225 --> 21:10.102
Well, I look forward
to having your badge

21:10.102 --> 21:12.438
after I win my lawsuit
against the LAPD.

21:12.438 --> 21:14.648
Hey, whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

21:14.648 --> 21:16.400
That stays here.
That's mine.

21:16.400 --> 21:18.402
No, it's <i>mine.</i>

21:18.402 --> 21:20.988
I paid for this.
I paid for all of that.

21:20.988 --> 21:23.324
Fine.

21:23.324 --> 21:28.788
♪♪

21:28.788 --> 21:34.210
♪♪

21:34.210 --> 21:36.378
Oh!
Want me to light them up?

21:36.378 --> 21:37.880
What?

21:37.880 --> 21:40.090
That green car
just made an illegal turn.

21:40.090 --> 21:42.510
Oh, uh...no.

21:44.136 --> 21:45.763
Are you okay?

21:45.763 --> 21:47.139
I mean,
you've been pretty quiet

21:47.139 --> 21:48.390
since we left
the hospital.

21:48.390 --> 21:50.768
[ Chuckles ]
Nah, it's just, uh...

21:50.768 --> 21:53.813
uh, I'm pregnant.

21:53.813 --> 21:55.314
[ Chuckles ]

21:55.314 --> 21:56.816
Oh!

21:56.816 --> 21:58.651
Congratulations?

21:58.651 --> 22:01.070
Yeah, I mean,
uh, they just

22:01.070 --> 22:02.988
told me
at the hospital.

22:02.988 --> 22:04.281
And it was unexpected,
huh?

22:04.281 --> 22:05.658
[ Sighs, scoffs ]

22:07.117 --> 22:10.996
Uh, after Lila, I had
some serious complications,

22:10.996 --> 22:15.125
and I was told
that I couldn't get pregnant.

22:15.125 --> 22:19.004
Clearly, I should have
followed up with a specialist.

22:19.004 --> 22:20.965
Are you worried about how James
is gonna take the news?

22:20.965 --> 22:24.134
James is amazing.

22:24.134 --> 22:27.304
But we've only been together
a few months, and I ‐‐

22:27.304 --> 22:29.431
we never thought that...
Yeah.

22:29.431 --> 22:32.309
That sounds like a lot
to process.

22:32.309 --> 22:33.602
Yeah.

22:33.602 --> 22:35.688
So, what are you
gonna do?

22:35.688 --> 22:39.233
Avoid dealing with it
until absolutely necessary.

22:39.233 --> 22:41.026
[ Chuckles ] Yeah.

22:41.026 --> 22:43.654
I use that method a lot.

22:43.654 --> 22:45.614
Martin: What the hell
am I doing here?

22:45.614 --> 22:48.617
Martin, are you familiar with
a girl named Becca Price?

22:48.617 --> 22:50.286
Uh, yeah.

22:50.286 --> 22:51.829
We're friends.

22:51.829 --> 22:54.331
Friends?
With an 18‐year‐old?

22:54.331 --> 22:55.541
How about she found you

22:55.541 --> 22:57.626
looking for sex on ClipTalk
a few months ago,

22:57.626 --> 22:59.503
and you've been hooking up
every now and then

22:59.503 --> 23:01.839
in exchange for letting her
sleep in your bed.

23:01.839 --> 23:03.007
Look,
what is she saying?

23:03.007 --> 23:04.300
<i>'Cause I don't know</i>
<i>if you know,</i>

23:04.300 --> 23:06.385
<i>but that girl is homeless,</i>
<i>unstable.</i>

23:06.385 --> 23:07.970
She's probably on drugs
or something.

23:07.970 --> 23:09.013
She's dead.

23:09.013 --> 23:10.848
What?

23:10.848 --> 23:12.016
I didn't ‐‐

23:12.016 --> 23:13.517
That wasn't me.

23:13.517 --> 23:14.894
Where were you
last night?

23:14.894 --> 23:17.855
At home.

23:17.855 --> 23:20.858
Look,
Becca did come over,

23:20.858 --> 23:22.276
but only
for a few minutes.

23:22.276 --> 23:23.569
I swear.

23:23.569 --> 23:25.070
What time?
Eight‐ish.

23:25.070 --> 23:26.614
It was definitely
before 9:00.

23:26.614 --> 23:28.407
That's when
my girlfriend got home.

23:28.407 --> 23:30.576
Your girlfriend?

23:30.576 --> 23:32.870
Yeah, she travels.
I get lonely.

23:32.870 --> 23:36.582
What did Becca want?
A place to sleep,
a shower.

23:36.582 --> 23:38.584
<i>I told her</i>
<i>my girlfriend was on her way.</i>

23:38.584 --> 23:39.877
Look, Becca threatened
to tell on me

23:39.877 --> 23:41.503
if I didn't
give her money.

23:41.503 --> 23:43.047
All I had was a 20.

23:43.047 --> 23:44.256
After she left,

23:44.256 --> 23:46.717
I realized she stole
my Cerus watch.

23:46.717 --> 23:48.093
<i>Cost me 10 grand.</i>

23:48.093 --> 23:49.803
<i>And you couldn't</i>
<i>file a police report</i>

23:49.803 --> 23:52.097
because you would have to
explain what happened

23:52.097 --> 23:53.557
to your girlfriend.

23:55.225 --> 23:57.770
Okay.
Sit tight.

23:57.770 --> 23:59.980
Please,
I didn't hurt that girl.

24:01.231 --> 24:02.942
You have to believe me.

24:02.942 --> 24:05.945
There was no watch
on Becca's body.

24:05.945 --> 24:07.446
Whoever killed her
probably took it.

24:07.446 --> 24:09.990
Or maybe she sold it.
Tamara might know where.

24:09.990 --> 24:13.077
Good news. They got inside
Jason's laptop

24:13.077 --> 24:15.955
and found a very intricate
money‐laundering operation.

24:15.955 --> 24:17.915
That's great.
Who's he working for?

24:17.915 --> 24:19.291
They can't tell yet.

24:19.291 --> 24:21.543
Jason works
a pretty skilled shell game.

24:21.543 --> 24:24.588
But Financial Crimes
are monitoring the accounts,

24:24.588 --> 24:26.632
and if he tries to move
any money, they'll track it.

24:26.632 --> 24:28.384
He won't.
He knows we have his laptop.

24:28.384 --> 24:29.760
He'll assume
you're watching.

24:29.760 --> 24:31.303
Well, he'll have to move
the money eventually.

24:31.303 --> 24:33.263
Whoever he's working for
is gonna expect results.

24:33.263 --> 24:34.890
So, what's his next move?

24:34.890 --> 24:37.434
I don't know.
Yet.

24:37.434 --> 24:39.603
Aaron: Uh‐oh.

24:39.603 --> 24:42.022
Looks like your avoidance plan
just hit a speed bump.

24:43.107 --> 24:44.858
Okay,
our first official fight.

24:44.858 --> 24:47.152
So, I'll lay out
the way I handle conflict,

24:47.152 --> 24:48.529
which is
to go right at it.

24:48.529 --> 24:50.322
I asked you
to let me handle

24:50.322 --> 24:52.157
the Curtis situation
by myself,

24:52.157 --> 24:54.118
but you ‐‐
you didn't listen.

24:54.118 --> 24:56.370
I ‐‐
Yeah, you were only there
in case something happened.

24:56.370 --> 24:58.288
I get it. Sure.
But that's not the point.

24:58.288 --> 25:00.791
I expressed my desire,
and you ignored it,

25:00.791 --> 25:02.209
and that pisses me off.

25:02.209 --> 25:04.294
I mean, if you don't trust me
when I tell you

25:04.294 --> 25:05.963
that I got
something handled,

25:05.963 --> 25:07.923
then that's something
that we gotta work out,

25:07.923 --> 25:09.591
because if we can't
trust each other ‐‐

25:09.591 --> 25:11.802
I'm pregnant.

25:11.802 --> 25:14.513
[ Inhales sharply ]

25:14.513 --> 25:17.808
I‐I‐I can't tell
if you're joking.

25:17.808 --> 25:19.768
I'm not.

25:21.478 --> 25:22.855
I just found out.

25:22.855 --> 25:25.024
Harper.
Uh, we need to go.

25:25.024 --> 25:26.650
My mom just sent
a 911 text,

25:26.650 --> 25:28.902
and she's not answering
her phone.

25:28.902 --> 25:32.239
Alright.
What's up?

25:34.033 --> 25:35.451
[ Sighs ]

25:37.995 --> 25:40.748
I'll call you
after my shift.

25:42.750 --> 25:46.670
Becca talked about you
all the time.

25:46.670 --> 25:48.047
Really?

25:48.047 --> 25:51.383
She was always wondering
what you were up to.

25:51.383 --> 25:53.510
She was so proud.

25:53.510 --> 25:56.055
It was kind of annoying,
actually.

25:56.055 --> 25:58.807
I was like, "Damn, why you
so obsessed with Tamara?

25:58.807 --> 26:00.184
Stop."

26:00.184 --> 26:02.478
[ Both chuckle ]

26:02.478 --> 26:03.854
But for real.

26:03.854 --> 26:05.481
We're all proud.

26:06.565 --> 26:08.692
I should've
stayed in better touch.

26:08.692 --> 26:10.861
I‐I'm sorry.

26:10.861 --> 26:13.405
[ Indistinct shouting ]

26:13.405 --> 26:15.240
[ Radio chatter ]

26:17.242 --> 26:20.079
Look out.
No. It's okay.

26:20.079 --> 26:21.330
They're cool.

26:23.248 --> 26:26.210
Hey.

26:26.210 --> 26:27.586
How are you
holding up?

26:27.586 --> 26:30.672
It's just a lot.
Being back here.

26:30.672 --> 26:33.217
Did you
find out anything?

26:33.217 --> 26:35.677
Yes. Uh, Lopez interviewed
all of the men

26:35.677 --> 26:37.012
that Becca
was swiping with.

26:37.012 --> 26:38.347
They all have
solid alibis.

26:38.347 --> 26:40.057
We did find out
that Becca stole a watch

26:40.057 --> 26:41.433
from one of them
right before she died,

26:41.433 --> 26:42.893
so if we can trace her
back there,

26:42.893 --> 26:44.770
we might be able to find out
what happened to her.

26:44.770 --> 26:46.230
Do you have any idea

26:46.230 --> 26:47.773
what Becca would have done
with a stolen watch?

26:49.358 --> 26:52.277
Tamara, hey.
Uh, it's okay.

26:52.277 --> 26:53.779
There's no
judgment here.

26:53.779 --> 26:57.116
Um...

26:57.116 --> 26:59.910
there's a pawn shop
we used to go to.

26:59.910 --> 27:01.286
Harvey's.

27:01.286 --> 27:03.580
It's just two blocks.

27:03.580 --> 27:05.457
Okay. Yeah.
We'll check it out.

27:05.457 --> 27:08.085
Are you okay here?

27:08.085 --> 27:10.254
Yeah. Yeah.
I'm good.

27:10.254 --> 27:11.588
Okay.

27:11.588 --> 27:13.382
Alright.

27:13.382 --> 27:15.300
[ Sighs ]

27:15.300 --> 27:18.262
♪ Catch a splash,
if it's 'bout me getting money ♪

27:18.262 --> 27:20.889
Do you still hear the lambs,
Clarice?

27:20.889 --> 27:22.516
Oh, Oscar,
you're no Hannibal Lecter.

27:22.516 --> 27:24.017
You're more
"Ernest Goes to Jail."

27:24.017 --> 27:26.603
Well, you still need my help,
so hit me.

27:26.603 --> 27:29.273
Jason was laundering money.
We shut it down.

27:29.273 --> 27:31.316
The arrest warrant's ready to
go. We just need to find him.

27:31.316 --> 27:34.486
Well, okay.
Well, let me think about that.

27:34.486 --> 27:36.822
I'm Jason. Right?

27:36.822 --> 27:38.824
My back
is against the wall.

27:38.824 --> 27:42.995
The people that I launder money
for are pissed, right?

27:42.995 --> 27:45.163
Probably want me dead.

27:45.163 --> 27:47.165
And the police
are moving in.

27:47.165 --> 27:50.335
So...what do I do?

27:52.754 --> 27:55.299
Honestly?
It's really simple.

27:55.299 --> 27:57.426
I just turn myself in.

27:57.426 --> 28:00.762
<i>Flip on my employers</i>
<i>and cut a sweet deal.</i>

28:00.762 --> 28:02.014
<i>John?</i>

28:02.014 --> 28:04.641
♪♪

28:08.353 --> 28:12.190
♪♪

28:12.190 --> 28:14.401
Well, you tell Ye
that I want in,

28:14.401 --> 28:16.236
so he should call me back.

28:16.236 --> 28:18.238
[ Telephone beeps ]
Aaron: Hey.

28:18.238 --> 28:20.490
I tried calling you.
What's wrong?

28:20.490 --> 28:21.700
Oh, nothing.

28:21.700 --> 28:24.912
I just have somebody
I would love for you to meet.

28:24.912 --> 28:27.247
Aaron.
I'm Morris Mackey.

28:27.247 --> 28:28.790
I'm the reality TV producer
here.

28:28.790 --> 28:30.250
It's nice
to finally meet you.

28:30.959 --> 28:32.044
You are?

28:32.044 --> 28:33.337
Annoyed.

28:33.337 --> 28:36.006
Right.
Uh, I'll make this quick.

28:36.006 --> 28:37.966
I want
to change your image.

28:37.966 --> 28:40.510
You've been the villain before,
you've been the victim,

28:40.510 --> 28:42.179
but you've never been
the hero.

28:42.179 --> 28:45.182
Let me make you
the hero of your own story.

28:45.182 --> 28:47.476
That's it.
Think about it, baby.

28:47.476 --> 28:50.020
[ Sighs ]

28:50.020 --> 28:52.481
<i>So, all parties here</i>
<i>are in agreement on the</i>
<i>terms of the deal ‐‐</i>

28:52.481 --> 28:55.025
you, Jason Wyler,
admit to residing in an address

28:55.025 --> 28:57.235
not registered
with your parole officer.

28:57.235 --> 28:59.071
<i>You admit to the crime</i>
<i>of laundering money</i>

28:59.071 --> 29:01.323
<i>for the Southern Front</i>
<i>criminal organization.</i>

29:01.323 --> 29:03.408
And you admit
to the crime of planting cocaine

29:03.408 --> 29:05.452
in a vehicle owned
by Bailey Nune.

29:05.452 --> 29:07.871
He does.

29:07.871 --> 29:11.416
And I regret
all of it.

29:11.416 --> 29:12.668
Oh, come on.

29:12.668 --> 29:14.252
<i>In exchange</i>
<i>for your cooperation</i>

29:14.252 --> 29:16.046
with an investigation
into Southern Front,

29:16.046 --> 29:17.381
we are prepared
to offer you

29:17.381 --> 29:18.840
a reduced sentence
of 18 months.

29:18.840 --> 29:20.509
18 months?

29:20.509 --> 29:22.761
He nearly ruined my life,
and that's all he gets?

29:22.761 --> 29:24.388
I know.
It sucks.

29:24.388 --> 29:26.056
But putting a dent
in an organization

29:26.056 --> 29:29.559
as evil as the Southern Front
is just far too...

29:29.559 --> 29:31.561
compelling for
the DA's office.

29:31.561 --> 29:33.063
This isn't gonna stop.

29:33.063 --> 29:35.148
The second he gets out,
he'll find me again.

29:35.148 --> 29:36.608
And we'll be ready
for him.

29:36.608 --> 29:38.777
Sgt. Grey: I'm gonna be
very clear, Mr. Wyler,

29:38.777 --> 29:40.904
so there's no confusion.

29:40.904 --> 29:43.615
If you try to pull anything
during the operation,

29:43.615 --> 29:47.077
this deal
and any sentiment of leniency

29:47.077 --> 29:50.455
we may be feeling toward you
is off the table.

29:50.455 --> 29:54.543
♪♪

29:54.543 --> 29:56.378
Do you understand?

29:56.378 --> 29:57.921
I understand, sir.

29:57.921 --> 29:59.256
And I promise you,

29:59.256 --> 30:02.759
you won't see
any tricks from me.

30:02.759 --> 30:05.929
♪♪

30:05.929 --> 30:07.639
Wesley:
Nyla's pregnant?

30:07.639 --> 30:09.141
Yeah.

30:09.141 --> 30:10.767
Congratulations.
[ Chuckles ]

30:10.767 --> 30:12.436
You guys
didn't waste any time.

30:12.436 --> 30:14.938
Oh.

30:14.938 --> 30:16.314
It wasn't planned.

30:16.314 --> 30:17.941
Not at all.
Mm.

30:17.941 --> 30:19.985
But ‐‐ But i‐it's great.

30:19.985 --> 30:21.278
Uh‐huh.

30:21.278 --> 30:22.863
You don't sound
very convincing.

30:22.863 --> 30:25.782
It's just ‐‐ she told me
in the middle of a fight.

30:25.782 --> 30:27.701
Oh.
Yeah, an argument bomb.

30:27.701 --> 30:29.494
Angela's dropped
a few of those on me.

30:29.494 --> 30:31.830
So,
how did you respond?

30:31.830 --> 30:34.374
I didn't.
[ Scoffs ]

30:34.374 --> 30:36.585
She told you she was pregnant,
and you didn't say anything?

30:36.585 --> 30:38.587
At all?

30:38.587 --> 30:40.297
♪♪

30:40.297 --> 30:42.174
Okay, so,
w‐w‐what should I do?

30:42.174 --> 30:43.550
It's big gesture time.

30:43.550 --> 30:45.969
You're gonna have to max your
credit card out on this one.

30:45.969 --> 30:48.263
[ Chuckles ] Man.

30:48.263 --> 30:51.641
Man:
<i>If you're just joining us...</i>

30:51.641 --> 30:54.936
Oh, hello, Officers.
Shopping around?

30:54.936 --> 30:57.522
Let me guess.
A Rams fan, am I right?

30:57.522 --> 30:59.399
Hey, I've got a signed copy
of Cooper Kupp's ‐‐

30:59.399 --> 31:01.526
We're looking for
a stolen Ceres watch,

31:01.526 --> 31:02.903
worth about 10 grand.

31:02.903 --> 31:06.073
So, you come into my shop,
accusing me?

31:06.073 --> 31:08.700
Lucy:
Of purchasing stolen property
from homeless teenagers?

31:08.700 --> 31:10.535
We are accusing you
of exactly that.

31:10.535 --> 31:12.704
Oh.
So I'm the bad guy?

31:12.704 --> 31:15.040
These kids got nobody
looking out for them.

31:15.040 --> 31:16.541
So what if something
falls into their hands

31:16.541 --> 31:18.168
that whoever owned it
won't miss?

31:18.168 --> 31:20.003
They're just
trying to survive.

31:20.003 --> 31:21.713
I'm a lifeline
to these kids.

31:21.713 --> 31:23.840
Were you a lifeline
to her?

31:23.840 --> 31:25.300
Oh, man.

31:25.300 --> 31:27.177
Is she dead?

31:27.177 --> 31:29.638
Yes. And the watch
could be the reason why.

31:29.638 --> 31:34.101
♪♪

31:34.101 --> 31:35.477
It was
brought in yesterday.

31:35.477 --> 31:40.315
♪♪

31:40.315 --> 31:42.400
The serial number matches.
Becca was here.

31:42.400 --> 31:43.693
No.

31:43.693 --> 31:46.363
I bought this
off Declan.

31:46.363 --> 31:47.864
♪♪

31:47.864 --> 31:50.909
Isn't that
Tamara's friend?

31:50.909 --> 31:53.411
Are you okay?
No.

31:53.411 --> 31:55.413
I miss her, too,

31:55.413 --> 31:59.042
and I'm so sorry
I haven't been around.

32:01.711 --> 32:03.922
She showed me
the watch.

32:03.922 --> 32:05.799
Said that she was gonna pawn it
in the morning

32:05.799 --> 32:09.386
and use the cash
to go back to school.

32:09.386 --> 32:11.763
Be like you, she said.

32:11.763 --> 32:13.056
Believe that?

32:13.056 --> 32:14.933
♪♪

32:14.933 --> 32:17.769
She was gonna
leave me, too.

32:17.769 --> 32:19.563
So, she went to sleep,

32:19.563 --> 32:22.816
and I tried
to sneak the watch out,

32:22.816 --> 32:27.070
but she woke up
and she totally freaked on me,

32:27.070 --> 32:30.115
so I‐I pushed her
and ‐‐ and she hit her head,

32:30.115 --> 32:31.449
and there was
so much blood.

32:31.449 --> 32:34.244
It ‐‐ It was an accident.
I swear that I didn't ‐‐

32:34.244 --> 32:36.746
Declan, show us your hands
right now.

32:36.746 --> 32:38.790
Turn around.

32:38.790 --> 32:41.376
Interlace your fingers
behind your head.

32:41.376 --> 32:42.878
♪♪

32:42.878 --> 32:44.421
[ Siren wailing ]
7‐Adam‐100.

32:44.421 --> 32:47.299
Show us Code 4.
Suspect in custody.

32:47.299 --> 32:49.050
Hey, are you okay?

32:49.050 --> 32:50.594
No.

32:50.594 --> 32:53.096
♪♪

32:56.808 --> 32:58.643
Sgt. Grey: So, we have to check
your mic levels.

32:58.643 --> 33:00.437
Can you
speak normally for me?

33:00.437 --> 33:03.148
This must be
killing you.

33:03.148 --> 33:05.692
Levels are fine.

33:05.692 --> 33:08.320
You talk to Officer Nolan again,
I'll pull your deal.

33:08.320 --> 33:09.696
Understood?

33:09.696 --> 33:11.823
Yes, sir.

33:11.823 --> 33:14.659
Now, shall we go over the plan
one last time, Mr. Wyler?

33:14.659 --> 33:17.120
I get them
to turn over the money,

33:17.120 --> 33:19.289
confirm turnaround
to the usual accounts,

33:19.289 --> 33:21.333
and you guys swoop in.

33:21.333 --> 33:22.959
In addition
to hearing every word,

33:22.959 --> 33:24.461
we've set up
a surveillance camera

33:24.461 --> 33:26.004
at the exchange point.

33:26.004 --> 33:28.590
Anything goes wrong,
we'll be in there quick,
fast, and in a hurry.

33:28.590 --> 33:30.425
I have no doubt,
Sergeant.

33:30.425 --> 33:32.469
Thank you for this.

33:32.469 --> 33:34.721
[ Sighs ]

33:44.314 --> 33:45.815
[ Sighs ]

33:45.815 --> 33:47.859
You know you don't have to
be here for this.

33:47.859 --> 33:50.153
Yes, sir.
Thank you.

33:50.153 --> 33:51.363
But I do.

33:51.363 --> 33:53.114
[ Radio clicks ]

33:53.114 --> 33:54.741
Friendly moving
into position.

33:56.534 --> 33:58.328
Harper:
7‐Adam‐19, copy.

33:58.328 --> 34:00.372
[ Radio clatters ]

34:00.372 --> 34:02.874
Okay, you need to get
your head in the game.

34:02.874 --> 34:05.001
Look at me. I just found out
I am pregnant,

34:05.001 --> 34:07.504
and yet, I am focused
and ready to go.

34:07.504 --> 34:09.214
Yes, ma'am.
I'm sorry.

34:10.840 --> 34:12.842
You gonna do the show?

34:12.842 --> 34:14.511
I don't know.

34:14.511 --> 34:17.347
I‐I just feel like it
would cheapen everything
I went through.

34:17.347 --> 34:19.808
Then why are you
still struggling?

34:19.808 --> 34:22.852
Because I feel like
I'm letting my mom down.

34:22.852 --> 34:24.229
And?

34:24.229 --> 34:26.189
Because if the show's
done right,

34:26.189 --> 34:29.067
then I can finally control
the way people see me.

34:29.067 --> 34:30.443
Hmm.

34:32.237 --> 34:34.072
[ Cellphone buzzes ]

34:35.198 --> 34:36.700
Not a good time,
Oscar.

34:36.700 --> 34:39.911
Oh, well, then I'll be fast.
Two words ‐‐ you're welcome.

34:39.911 --> 34:41.413
What am I supposed to be
thanking you for?

34:41.413 --> 34:43.581
<i>Well, after doing a little</i>
<i>digging on your boy Jason,</i>

34:43.581 --> 34:45.250
I found out
he has a side hustle

34:45.250 --> 34:46.710
working with
the Southern Front.

34:46.710 --> 34:48.545
The same group
of fine young folks

34:48.545 --> 34:50.171
that want
your pal Oscar dead.

34:50.171 --> 34:51.548
Officer Nolan,
the target has arrived.

34:51.548 --> 34:53.008
Sir,
we may have a problem.

34:53.008 --> 34:55.093
Oscar, cut to the chase.
What did you do?

34:55.093 --> 34:56.553
Oh, fine.
Ruin my story.

34:56.553 --> 34:58.096
Okay, upshot is,

34:58.096 --> 35:00.098
I think I found a solution
to both of our problems.

35:00.098 --> 35:01.891
<i>A few minutes ago,</i>
<i>I had a little talk</i>

35:01.891 --> 35:03.184
<i>with a Southern Front contact.</i>

35:03.184 --> 35:04.477
<i>I told them your boy Jason</i>

35:04.477 --> 35:06.730
was working with the cops
to rat them out.

35:06.730 --> 35:09.107
<i>And in exchange,</i>
<i>they lifted the hit on me,</i>

35:09.107 --> 35:10.442
<i>put one out on him.</i>

35:10.442 --> 35:13.612
Two birds,
one shiv, huh?

35:13.612 --> 35:16.239
All units,
the friendly's been made.

35:16.239 --> 35:17.616
Move in.

35:17.616 --> 35:22.078
♪♪

35:22.078 --> 35:24.080
♪ Another year, another year ♪

35:24.080 --> 35:25.749
How much
we looking at?

35:25.749 --> 35:27.626
About two mil.

35:27.626 --> 35:29.210
Same accounts
as last time?

35:29.210 --> 35:31.254
[ Cellphone buzzing ]

35:31.254 --> 35:35.592
♪ From the start,
another drag, another drag ♪

35:35.592 --> 35:36.676
What?

35:36.676 --> 35:38.303
[ Scoffs ]

35:38.303 --> 35:40.472
♪ Another glass, another glass ♪

35:40.472 --> 35:42.432
Is there a problem?
Yeah.

35:42.432 --> 35:43.725
Apparently, it's you.

35:43.725 --> 35:45.393
Okay.
Police!

35:45.393 --> 35:46.895
[ Siren wailing ]

35:46.895 --> 35:49.606
[ Gunshots ]

35:49.606 --> 35:52.567
♪ Another year ♪

35:53.610 --> 35:55.945
Drop your weapons!
Now!

35:55.945 --> 35:57.155
♪ Another party ♪

35:57.155 --> 35:58.615
Cover me.

35:58.615 --> 36:01.868
♪ Another clown,
another clown ♪

36:01.868 --> 36:04.913
♪ Always taking it too far ♪

36:04.913 --> 36:07.332
♪ Another life, another life ♪

36:07.332 --> 36:09.751
♪ When will it start ♪

36:09.751 --> 36:12.087
♪ Another wish, another wish ♪

36:12.087 --> 36:13.922
♪ I never wanted anything ♪

36:13.922 --> 36:15.632
Put it down!

36:15.632 --> 36:18.259
On the ground!
Right now! Get down!

36:18.259 --> 36:19.969
Get down, right now!
On the ground!

36:19.969 --> 36:21.471
Down!

36:21.471 --> 36:25.141
♪ Another year ♪

36:25.141 --> 36:28.186
♪ Don't wanna be
your birthday boy ♪

36:28.186 --> 36:30.897
♪ Don't wanna be
